title: Correct RMR/SRMR, add MAR/SMAR fit indices
body:
RMR/SRMR should be computed on only the unique elements of the residuals matrices. 

Also added mean absolute residual fit indices (reported by EQS, seem to be less positively biased than SRMR based on some quick simulations).

title: ACTUALLY working plot method for Windows.
body:
Hey Tim,

This is tested on Windows.  I also wrote a single function for the part of the code I was working on that was repetitive.  Test it on Mac; it should still work.  Boy, there was a lot of fiddling that had to be done to get it working on Windows.  Glad I did it!  It would've take weeks to figure out by going back and forth over email.

May want to adjust some of the GraphViz defaults.  The value on the covariance path intersects with the path.

[tim.dot.pdf](https://github.com/tbates/umx/files/120495/tim.dot.pdf)

Cheers,
Mike Hunter
